Description: Lightweight Signal daemon for OpenClaw AI integration
 Signal Gateway is a high-performance Signal messaging bridge designed
 for the Jetson Nano platform. It provides a RESTful API and Server-Sent
 Events (SSE) stream for bidirectional Signal communication with the
 OpenClaw AI assistant.
 .
 Key features:
 .
  - Automatic Signal receiver startup with 5-retry exponential backoff
  - Phone number to UUID resolution with caching
  - HTTP + JSON-RPC API for sending messages
  - SSE message stream for real-time receiving
  - Integration with Brain Server for AI-powered responses
  - Clean shutdown in under 100ms
  - Production-ready systemd integration
  - Rate limiting and input validation
 .
 This package includes the signal-gateway binary, wrapper script, and
 systemd service file. Configuration files are installed to
 /etc/signal-gateway/ and Signal data to /var/lib/signal-gateway/.
 .
 On first run, you will need to link your Signal device by scanning
 a QR code displayed in the logs.
